						<summary>

						<p>Fragment of a slab lying by the side of a cart track about a kilometer to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to 17th century on the basis of the palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. Seems to register the gift of a <hi rend="italic">vṛitti</hi> and flower garden to the temple of Chennakēśavadēva on the occasion of the consecration of the god therein.</p>						

						</summary>
